The Khoisan Defiance Campaign will be leading a march against racism on Saturday at Langebaan, on the West Coast. The group say they will be calling on police to address the slow progress and lack of arrests in alleged racist incidents in Langebaan. Springbok Lock, Eben Etzebeth was accused of hate speech and assaulting two men outside a local pub in August.   Spokesperson for the Khoisan Defiance Campaign, Sammy Claasen says the group wants the immediate arrest of those implicated in the brutal assault case. “The community is marching to the police to hand over a memorandum to say that we want the immediate arrest of those implicated in the brutal assault case against people in Langebaan.”  Click on the video below: 